{
  "text": "Research conducted during the past three decades shows an increasing number of new and combined MADM techniques with different classifications (e.g., [CITATION_1] , most of which belong to the categories of multi-attribute utility (utility-based); Outranking; and mixed (compromise) methods. [CITATION_2] classify these methods in the three categories of utility features, outranking relationships and models of decision principles. While [CITATION_3] , and [CITATION_4] categorise them as: 1 the value and utility theory (known as 'American school' techniques) 2 uutranking (a.k.a. 'European school' techniques) 3 interactive approaches.",
